The Lagos State Government has announced COVID-19 test centres in its 20 Local Government Areas.
It however said visit to the centres is ‘strictly” by appointment, not emergency in a tweet on its official handle on Sunday. To book the appointment, residents were told to make requests through app.alertclinic.com at the test centre closest to them. Lagos has recorded 309 cases, 94 recoveries and 14 fatalities, making it the epicentre of coronavirus in Nigeria. COVID-19 TEST CENTRES IN LAGOS STATE